CATION OF THE USER OF INFORMATION.     DISCUSSES DEVELOPMENTS IN USER EDUCATION SINCE 1926, WHEN IT 1ST BECAME ASERIOUS STUDY, AND PAYS PARTICULAR ATTENTION TO ACTIVITIES WHICH FOLLOWED THEINTERNATIONAL ACCEPTANCE OF THE CONCEPT OF UNISIST IN 1971. PRESENTS THEFINDINGS OF 2 SURVEYS CARRIED OUT TO DISCOVER THE EXTENT TO WHICH COLLEGESTUDENTS AND WORKING SCIENTISTS IN PAKISTAN RECEIVED ANY FORMAL LIBRARY USEREDUCATION, AND PUTS FORWARD A PLAN FOR A NATIONAL USER EDUCATION PROGRAMME INTHAT COUNTRY